Whats driving company specific returns todayCRM DATA Following Googles acquisition of Looker last week Salesforce announced it is going to buy Tableau DATA in an all stock transaction with enterprise value of 157B Class A and Class B common stock of DATA will be exchanged for 1103 shares of CRM The transaction is intended to be tax free for Tableau stockholders and is expected to be completed during Salesforces fiscal third quarter ending October 31 2019

Whats driving general equity marketsStock markets are trading higher on Monday after the US abandoned plans to impose tariffs on Mexican goods A number of MA deals including a merger between United Technologies UTX and Raytheon RTN and Salesforce CRM and Tableau DATA added to the upbeat mood There are several very key releases this week including CPI trade prices retail sales and industrial production
